The Vice President, Mike Pence, attended an event at the Indiana Convention Center in Indianapolis to thank the American Legion Women's Auxiliary for their support of military families. He specifically thanked them for awarding the American Legion Women's Auxiliary Spirit Award to Karen Pence, the Second Lady of the United States, who has been actively involved in supporting military families. Pence praised Karen Pence for her public service and her efforts to support charitable causes. He also highlighted her work in meeting with families of servicemen and women across the country to ensure they receive recognition and support. Pence expressed his gratitude for the recognition of Karen Pence's dedication to military families and emphasized the importance of supporting and strengthening these families for the security of the nation.